This paper is about generating paraphrases using machine learning techniques. The most relevant sub-category is likely to be "cs.CL" (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning, reinforcement learning, and imitation learning, which are all subfields of machine learning. Therefore, "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a decoder to generate sentences, which falls under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The use of RL and IL also suggests "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and "cs.SD" (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories.
